div1.p:
Q. Did you leave any body in the mill? - A. Yes;
James Sharpe
was at work in the mill; I went into an opposite house about twelve o'clock.

Q. What are you? - A. Master of St. Bride's workhouse;
Thomas Heasty
died in our workhouse on the 15th of June; he told me himself that he was an out-pensioner of Chelsea Hospital - (The receipt read.)

Prisoner. Finch says he gave me thirty shillings for it; he only gave me twenty-six; he knew it to be stolen, and asked me if I had stolen it; I said, I had;
William Hollis
, of Shoemaker-row, took me down to him to sell it, and he wanted me to get him two gold seals.
